dlinkSwMgmdSnoopingMIB.name: dlinkSwMgmdSnoopingMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file for 'MGMD snooping' functionality.

dlinkSwMgmdSnoopingMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwMgmdSnoopingMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for MGMD (Multicast Group Membership Discovery) snooping.

SnoopingType.name: SnoopingType
SnoopingType.description: The snooping type. 'igmpSnooping' -- IGMP (IPv4 MGMD) snooping. 'mldSnooping' -- MLD (IPv6 MGMD) snooping.

dMgmdSnpStateGblEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpStateGblEnabled
dMgmdSnpStateGblEnabled.description: An object indicates which type of MGMD is globally enabled. Setting a type's bit to 1 means the type of MGMD is globally enabled. ipv4 (0) - IGMP snooping ipv6 (1) - MLD snooping.

dMgmdSnpClearAllState.name: dMgmdSnpClearAllState
dMgmdSnpClearAllState.description: This object indicates the global state of MGMD snooping statistics function. Configuring this object to igmpClear or mldClear will clear all respective MGMD snooping counters.

dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByPortIf.name: dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByPortIf
dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByPortIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the port/port-channel on which the IGMP snooping counters will be cleared. When read, the special value 0 is returned.

dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByPortIf.name: dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByPortIf
dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByPortIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the port/port-channel on which the MLD snooping counters will be cleared. When read, the special value 0 is returned.

dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByVlanId.name: dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByVlanId
dMgmdSnpClearIgmpSnoopByVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID on which the IGMP snooping counters will be cleared. When read, the special value 0 is returned.

dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByVlanId.name: dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByVlanId
dMgmdSnpClearMldSnoopByVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID on which the MLD snooping counters will be cleared. When read, the special value 0 is returned.

dMgmdSnpIfTable.name: dMgmdSnpIfTable
dMgmdSnpIfTable.description: This table lists the MGMD snooping settings per interface. An entry is created to configure the MGMD snooping related settings to different value than the default per interface. When an entry is deleted, all the MGMD snooping settings will be reverted to default settings.

dMgmdSnpIfEntry.name: dMgmdSnpIfEntry
dMgmdSnpIfEntry.description: A table entry represents the MGMD snooping state on a VLAN basis.

dMgmdSnpIfSnoopingType.name: dMgmdSnpIfSnoopingType
dMgmdSnpIfSnoopingType.description: The snooping type of this entry.

dMgmdSnpIfRowStatus.name: dMgmdSnpIfRowStatus
dMgmdSnpIfRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dMgmdSnpIfStateEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfStateEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfStateEnabled.description: This object indicates the state of MGMD snooping of the entry.

dMgmdSnpIfQuerierStateEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfQuerierStateEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfQuerierStateEnabled.description: This object indicates the MGMD query function in Layer 2 networks.

dMgmdSnpIfQuerierRouter.name: dMgmdSnpIfQuerierRouter
dMgmdSnpIfQuerierRouter.description: Indicates the VLAN interface at the switch system works as a MGMD querier or not. A value of absence(1) indicates the absence of this attribute.

dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveEnabled.description: This object enables the MGMD snooping fast-leave feature on the interface.

dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveHostBased.name: dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveHostBased
dMgmdSnpIfFastLeaveHostBased.description: This object configures the MGMD Snooping Host Based Fast Leave function.

dMgmdSnpIfMinimumVersion.name: dMgmdSnpIfMinimumVersion
dMgmdSnpIfMinimumVersion.description: To restrict the minimum version allows user to control the minimum version of MGMD hosts can be joined on a layer 2 port. The value '0' means that this interface does not restrict the minimum version. Value 2 applies to IGMP routers only. Value 3 applies to IGMP and MLD routers.

dMgmdSnpIfExplicitTrackEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfExplicitTrackEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfExplicitTrackEnabled.description: This object enables explicit tracking of group membership for IGMP Version 3 hosts on the interface.

dMgmdSnpIfReportSuppresEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfReportSuppresEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfReportSuppresEnabled.description: This object enables the report suppression on the interface.

dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportingEnabled.name: dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportingEnabled
dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportingEnabled.description: This object enables the proxy-reporting function on the interface.

dMgmdSnpIfAutoLearnMrouter.name: dMgmdSnpIfAutoLearnMrouter
dMgmdSnpIfAutoLearnMrouter.description: This object enables dynamically learning of multicast router port on the interface.

dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddrType.name: dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddrType
dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of Internet address of the source IP of proxy reporting.

dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddr.name: dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddr
dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportSrcAddr.description: This object indicates the source Internet address of proxy reporting. This object is valid when dMgmdSnpIfProxyReportingEnabled is 'true'.

dMgmdSnpIfQueryInterval.name: dMgmdSnpIfQueryInterval
dMgmdSnpIfQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP or MLD Query packets are transmitted on this interface.

dMgmdSnpIfQueryMaxResponseTime.name: dMgmdSnpIfQueryMaxResponseTime
dMgmdSnpIfQueryMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response interval advertised in IGMP or MLD queries on this interface.

dMgmdSnpIfQueryVersion.name: dMgmdSnpIfQueryVersion
dMgmdSnpIfQueryVersion.description: The version of MGMD querier version on this interface. Value 1 applies to IGMPv1 routers only. Value 2 applies to IGMPv2 and MLDv1 routers, and value 3 applies to IGMPv3 and MLDv2 routers.

dMgmdSnpIfRobustness.name: dMgmdSnpIfRobustness
dMgmdSnpIfRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet.

dMgmdSnpIfLastMemberQueryInterval.name: dMgmdSnpIfLastMemberQueryInterval
dMgmdSnpIfLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The amount of time between group-specific query messages. This value can be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network.

dMgmdSnpIfSuppressionTime.name: dMgmdSnpIfSuppressionTime
dMgmdSnpIfSuppressionTime.description: The interval of report suppression on this interface.

dMgmdSnpMrouterTable.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterTable
dMgmdSnpMrouterTable.description: The table to display and configure the MGMD snooping multicast router information. An entry is created if a multicast router is is learned dynamically on that port/port-channel interface (dMgmdSnpIfAutoLearnMrouter is 'true' on the VLAN interface). In this situation, an entry cannot be destroyed. An entry can also be created to statically configured a multicast router port or forbid a port/port-channel become multicast router port.

dMgmdSnpMrouterIfIndex.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterIfIndex
dMgmdSnpMrouterIfIndex.description: Indicates the specific physical port/port-channel interface

dMgmdSnpMrouterQuerierType.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterQuerierType
dMgmdSnpMrouterQuerierType.description: The snooping type of this interface.

dMgmdSnpMrouterStatus.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterStatus
dMgmdSnpMrouterStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dMgmdSnpMrouterAdminState.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterAdminState
dMgmdSnpMrouterAdminState.description: This object indicates the static configuration about multicast router state of a port/port-channel on a per-VLAN basis. none(1) - no static configuration designated(2) - the port/port-channel is a static multicast router port. forbidden(3) - the port/port-channel cannot be multicast router port.

dMgmdSnpMrouterDynamicMrouter.name: dMgmdSnpMrouterDynamicMrouter
dMgmdSnpMrouterDynamicMrouter.description: This object is valid when dMgmdSnpMrouterAdminState is 'none'. This object indicates the port/port-channel is dynamically learned as a multicast router port on the corresponding VLAN interface.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitTable.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitTable
dMgmdSnpIfLimitTable.description: The table to set the limitation on the number of MGMD cache entries. For a Layer 2 VLAN on a trunk port, the limitation can be set per port/port-channel and on per VLAN basis.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitIfIndex.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitIfIndex
dMgmdSnpIfLimitIfIndex.description: Indicates the specific physical interface/port-channel interface.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitVlanId.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitVlanId
dMgmdSnpIfLimitVlanId.description: Indicates the specific VLAN ID. A value of zero indicates that no VLAN ID is not applicable or not configured.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitRowStatus.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitRowStatus
dMgmdSnpIfLimitRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitExceptAccLstName.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitExceptAccLstName
dMgmdSnpIfLimitExceptAccLstName.description: The name of the IP/IPv6 basic access list. The group (*,G), or channel (S,G) permitted by the access list will be excluded from the limit. The zero length of this object means except ACL is not specified.

dMgmdSnpIfLimitValue.name: dMgmdSnpIfLimitValue
dMgmdSnpIfLimitValue.description: To restric the number of MGMD groups or channels allows user to control how many MGMD groups or channels can be joined on a layer-2 port.

dMgmdSnpAccGrpTable.name: dMgmdSnpAccGrpTable
dMgmdSnpAccGrpTable.description: The table to display and configure the IP/IPv6 basic access list information of MGMD snooping. For a Layer 2 VLAN on a trunk port, the access group can be set per port/port-channel and on per VLAN basis.

dMgmdSnpAccGrpIfIndex.name: dMgmdSnpAccGrpIfIndex
dMgmdSnpAccGrpIfIndex.description: Indicates the specific physical interface/port-channel interface.

dMgmdSnpAccGrpStatus.name: dMgmdSnpAccGrpStatus
dMgmdSnpAccGrpStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dMgmdSnpAccessGroupName.name: dMgmdSnpAccessGroupName
dMgmdSnpAccessGroupName.description: The name of the IP/IPv6 basic access list to be configured on MGMD snooping.

dMgmdSnpGroupTable.name: dMgmdSnpGroupTable
dMgmdSnpGroupTable.description: The table listing the MGMD snooping dynamic groups.

dMgmdSnpGroupAddressType.name: dMgmdSnpGroupAddressType
dMgmdSnpGroupAddressType.description: The type of this group address.

dMgmdSnpGroupAddress.name: dMgmdSnpGroupAddress
dMgmdSnpGroupAddress.description: This object identifies the group address of the entry.

dMgmdSnpGroupIfIndex.name: dMgmdSnpGroupIfIndex
dMgmdSnpGroupIfIndex.description: Indicates the specific physical port/port-channel interface

dMgmdSnpGroupVersion.name: dMgmdSnpGroupVersion
dMgmdSnpGroupVersion.description: The version of MGMD that the multicast group is reported.

dMgmdSnpGroupUpTime.name: dMgmdSnpGroupUpTime
dMgmdSnpGroupUpTime.description: The time elapsed since the entry has been created.

dMgmdSnpGroupExpire.name: dMgmdSnpGroupExpire
dMgmdSnpGroupExpire.description: The time that the entry will be removed if there is no refresh on the entry

dMgmdSnpGroupMode.name: dMgmdSnpGroupMode
dMgmdSnpGroupMode.description: The group mode is based on the type of membership reports that are received on the interface for the group.

dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddrType.name: dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddrType
dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of the last host to report being a member of the multicast group.

dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddr.name: dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddr
dMgmdSnpGroupLastReportAddr.description: This object indicates the address of the last host to report being a member of the multicast group.

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcTable.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcTable
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcTable.description: The table listing the MGMD snooping dynamic group source entries.

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddrType.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddrType
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of the source address where the (S,G) channel traffic originate.

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddress.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddress
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcAddress.description: This object indicates the source address where the (S,G) channel traffic originate.

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcIfIndex.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcIfIndex
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcIfIndex.description: Indicates the specific physical port/port-channel interface

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcUpTime.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcUpTime
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcUpTime.description: The time elapsed since the entry has been created.

dMgmdSnpGroupSrcForward.name: dMgmdSnpGroupSrcForward
dMgmdSnpGroupSrcForward.description: The status of whether the router is forwarding multicast traffic due to this entry.

dMgmdSnpStaticGrpTable.name: dMgmdSnpStaticGrpTable

dMgmdSnpHostGrpAddressType.name: dMgmdSnpHostGrpAddressType

dMgmdSnpHostGrpAddress.name: dMgmdSnpHostGrpAddress
